Colour.
Preserved animals show distinct black pigmentation in the prostomium, in the anterior part of the eyes, and in the subdistal ends of the tentacular cirri (
Fig. 9A
). The colouration is more distinct in the parapodial dorsal cirri of large individuals (
Fig. 9B
). Living specimens show green pigmentation especially on inter-segmental areas and dorsal cirri (
Fig. 8
).
